2
00:00:00,390 --> 00:00:05,850
[Buwahahaha, a request from your Excellency. Turn on the room lights and keep your distance from the TV when watching the show.]

3
00:00:00,960 --> 00:00:05,200
Why? Why must this happen to me?

4
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:07,140
Did I do something wrong?

5
00:00:07,360 --> 00:00:12,390
I'm forced to work in some inn for Stands. I'm told I'm useless and I'm tired,

6
00:00:12,390 --> 00:00:15,170
but I can't sleep because of them playing UNO every single night.

7
00:00:15,170 --> 00:00:18,590
If that weren't bad enough, I've been living on rice crackers and peanuts!

8
00:00:18,590 --> 00:00:22,140
I can't take it anymore.  I can't stay quiet.

9
00:00:22,140 --> 00:00:26,230
I'm going to do it. "His Excellency" and crap don't matter anymore.

10
00:00:26,230 --> 00:00:30,410
I'm going to crush this hot spring inn!

11
00:00:37,930 --> 00:00:40,930
Brief Trio, you've double-crossed me...

12
00:00:40,930 --> 00:00:46,220
If you want to defeat me, you need the help of the most powerful Stand.

13
00:00:46,220 --> 00:00:53,560
But that's impossible. There isn't anyone in Senbokyo who will help you.

14
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:59,790
I'm going to have you work here until you die.

15
00:00:59,790 --> 00:01:04,270
The most powerful Stand. The most powerful ally.

16
00:01:04,270 --> 00:01:05,830
Such a person...

17
00:01:06,350 --> 00:01:08,770
Huh? What are you doing here?

18
00:01:08,770 --> 00:01:10,250
Are you awake?

19
00:01:10,250 --> 00:01:12,290
You stink. What is that smell?

20
00:01:18,590 --> 00:01:20,380
They're in front of me!

21
00:03:01,090 --> 00:03:04,090
Stay in here for a while to cool down, Rei.

22
00:03:06,290 --> 00:03:12,470
I can't believe what you did. I never thought you'd double-cross me.

23
00:03:13,170 --> 00:03:16,080
I didn't double-cross you.

24
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:17,300
Don't get carried away!

25
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:22,440
Who do you think made you stay here?

26
00:03:23,090 --> 00:03:25,350
I wasn't working here because I wanted to.

27
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:27,730
Okami, you're the one who started all of this...

28
00:03:27,730 --> 00:03:28,430
Hush!

29
00:03:29,660 --> 00:03:33,740
We've been together for a long time, so you're getting off easily.

30
00:03:34,490 --> 00:03:38,430
Otherwise, I would have killed you off and your little soul, too!

31
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:41,770
You should be thankful I had mercy on you!

32
00:03:45,710 --> 00:03:48,140
This is wrong.

33
00:03:48,410 --> 00:03:49,760
What?

34
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:53,220
I said, this is wrong. You used to be...

35
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:56,050
Cut it out now.

36
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:59,470
If you don't, I won't be able to forgive you.

37
00:04:01,580 --> 00:04:05,750
Okami, you and this place have changed.

38
00:04:06,350 --> 00:04:08,670
Nothing has changed.

39
00:04:09,430 --> 00:04:13,780
In fact, we purposely tried not to change.

40
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:16,880
It's useless!

41
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:19,800
Even if you confine me in here, you can't stop him!

42
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:22,810
Gin... Gin will do something to save this inn!

43
00:04:23,470 --> 00:04:26,970
[Seal]

44
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:27,310
Sorry to say this, Rei...

45
00:04:28,890 --> 00:04:30,660
...he's become...

46
00:04:30,660 --> 00:04:32,920
...a pet dog without fangs.

47
00:04:33,430 --> 00:04:39,000
["Gin and His Excellency's Good-for-nothings."]

48
00:04:43,890 --> 00:04:45,810
[Banquet Hall]

49
00:04:49,940 --> 00:04:51,940
Way to go, Taishogun!

50
00:04:51,940 --> 00:04:56,390
It's as if you were drinking in the whole country! We admire you!

51
00:04:56,630 --> 00:05:00,260
Hey! Bring more sake! We need more!

52
00:05:00,260 --> 00:05:02,220
Lord Ieyasu, have another shot.

53
00:05:02,220 --> 00:05:05,530
Thank you, but have some yourself, Sir Nobunaga.

54
00:05:05,530 --> 00:05:06,950
Let me pour some for you.

55
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:08,620
No, I'll pour more for you.

56
00:05:08,620 --> 00:05:10,160
No, no. Let me do it.

57
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:12,310
Hey, bring more food and sake!

58
00:05:12,310 --> 00:05:13,780
Boy, we're so busy.

59
00:05:13,780 --> 00:05:16,020
Indeed. We need all the help we can get.

60
00:05:17,110 --> 00:05:19,520
How're my young people doing?

61
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:21,780
Have they've been somewhat helpful?

62
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:25,930
I did ask you to send a lively guy.

63
00:05:25,930 --> 00:05:30,640
But I don't remember asking for a mad dog that bites its owner, Otose.

64
00:05:32,230 --> 00:05:34,330
Oh, is he a little wilder than you expected?

65
00:05:34,330 --> 00:05:39,930
But I thought you needed a bulldog, not a calm little lap dog.

66
00:05:41,140 --> 00:05:45,160
Maybe. But he continually bit me severely.

67
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:48,010
So, I'll only pay you half of the referral fee.

68
00:05:48,010 --> 00:05:49,880
That's not the way I remember it!

69
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:51,980
That's your fault!

70
00:05:51,980 --> 00:05:55,760
Although we were shorthanded, I sent them all to you.

71
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:57,800
You need to pay as we agreed.

72
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:02,840
You sent me a defective worker, and I disciplined him.

73
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:04,670
I'd say you should pay me instead.

74
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:06,680
"Disciplined him?"

75
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:12,680
Right! I punished him a bit, and then he became completely obedient.

76
00:06:13,250 --> 00:06:15,890
He seems to like my place.

77
00:06:15,890 --> 00:06:19,500
And he said he didn't want to go back to you. What should I do?

78
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:24,000
Wait. I told you that you could have them for only ten days.

79
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,810
But that's what he wants. I can't do anything about it.

80
00:06:29,090 --> 00:06:31,820
Oiwa, have you...

81
00:06:32,810 --> 00:06:34,520
...fallen for him?

82
00:06:39,030 --> 00:06:42,660
Otose, I can't hide anything from you, can I?

83
00:06:42,660 --> 00:06:44,970
Where did you find that man?

84
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:49,740
He's allied himself with my most trusted worker in a short period.

85
00:06:49,740 --> 00:06:54,000
And then he plotted to revolt against me. No ordinary man can achieve such a thing.

86
00:06:54,970 --> 00:06:58,560
Right now he's a useless good-for-nothing.

87
00:06:59,330 --> 00:07:02,940
But with a bit of training, he'll become a fearsome monster.

88
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:08,850
I can't think of anyone better to take over for me.

89
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:11,350
Otose...

90
00:07:16,900 --> 00:07:18,070
Back then,

91
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:20,310
you stole away your husband-to-be.

92
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:26,080
But this time, I get to take the man.

93
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:29,910
He's my dog now.

94
00:07:29,910 --> 00:07:32,980
That man will have to work the rest of his life in this inn.

95
00:07:37,990 --> 00:07:39,440
That helps me.

96
00:07:42,630 --> 00:07:46,190
As long as you send the woman and child back to me, it's fine.

97
00:07:46,190 --> 00:07:48,240
You can do whatever you want to him.

98
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:50,800
If I can get rid of that lousy slacker who doesn't pay his rent,

99
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:53,680
then there's nothing happier than this.

100
00:07:54,350 --> 00:08:00,970
But let me point out one thing. That man is fierce.

101
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:04,000
I already disciplined him.

102
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:07,060
Even if he wanted to bite me, he doesn't have fangs anymore.

103
00:08:08,590 --> 00:08:12,580
Oiwa, it doesn't matter how many fangs you broke.

104
00:08:13,170 --> 00:08:19,120
You can discipline a beast, but he's not just a beast. He's worse.

105
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:21,680
He's a wild animal.

106
00:08:22,930 --> 00:08:27,000
Okami! Gin broke out of the punishment room and escaped!

107
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:30,520
That's what I told you. You'd better be careful.

108
00:08:33,390 --> 00:08:34,930
Find him!

109
00:08:34,930 --> 00:08:37,120
It would have been impossible for him to go down the mountain!

110
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:39,520
He must be somewhere in this inn!

111
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:41,640
Look everywhere!

112
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:45,030
Gin, how did he manage to slip out of the punishment room?!

113
00:08:45,030 --> 00:08:46,970
I trapped Rei in the spell bind cell.

114
00:08:47,190 --> 00:08:50,680
And the others are supposed to be possessed by Stands, playing UNO.

115
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:55,640
He couldn't have had any help. So how did he do it?!

116
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:00,940
This is...

117
00:09:00,940 --> 00:09:02,170
Don't tell me...

118
00:09:04,890 --> 00:09:08,780
Oh, here we go, here, here.

119
00:09:05,490 --> 00:09:09,640
Here we go, here, here!

120
00:09:09,640 --> 00:09:12,640
This is... Why are they here?!

121
00:09:13,890 --> 00:09:16,720
They're supposed to be possessed by Stands, playing UNO!

122
00:09:17,690 --> 00:09:20,170
No, they're Stands?!

123
00:09:20,570 --> 00:09:24,420
It can't be! How could they be Stands when they're not even dead?!

124
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:29,280
Can it be, that they helped Gin?!

125
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:30,560
They're living ghosts.

126
00:09:31,530 --> 00:09:37,550
Being possessed by a Stand means to have a foreign spirit enter your body.

127
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,300
And because of it,

128
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:45,180
their original Stands rejected themselves from the body, escaping as living ghosts.

129
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:47,650
No.

130
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:51,200
Even if this place is one of the foremost spiritual sites in Japan,

131
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:54,810
that can't be the only reason for them to become Stands.

132
00:09:56,780 --> 00:09:58,480
Don't tell me,

133
00:09:58,480 --> 00:10:01,630
they went out of their way to become Stands because they wanted to help him?!

134
00:10:02,270 --> 00:10:04,010
It can't be!

135
00:10:04,010 --> 00:10:06,560
Oh, how fun this is!

136
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:10,510
This is the most fun party I've ever been to since I was born.

137
00:10:10,510 --> 00:10:12,110
What are you talking about?

138
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:17,640
It's not since you were born. Don't you mean since you've died?

139
00:10:19,450 --> 00:10:21,580
Shoot, you're right!

140
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:24,260
What?!

141
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:26,680
Lord Ieyasu has disappeared!

142
00:10:27,140 --> 00:10:29,310
And the other guests are disappearing!

143
00:10:30,670 --> 00:10:35,300
It can't be! That man found out how to defeat the Stands?!

144
00:10:36,250 --> 00:10:37,550
That's right.

145
00:10:37,550 --> 00:10:42,550
You don't defeat Stands by holding them down by physical force,

146
00:10:42,550 --> 00:10:45,400
or to trick them by using your head.

147
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:46,400
Defeating Stands means

148
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:49,180
sending them to heaven.

149
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:52,600
The Stands wander this world because of their regrets.

150
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:56,810
Only when they feel satisfied and happy can they go into heaven.

151
00:10:56,810 --> 00:11:00,770
Yes. You don't need muscle and intelligence to defeat Stands.

152
00:11:00,770 --> 00:11:02,380
All you need is...

153
00:11:03,310 --> 00:11:07,010
[Sympathy]
[Consideration]
[Kindness]

154
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:06,440
sympathy, consideration or kindness.

155
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:10,800
The kind of things you learn in class become the ultimate weapons!

156
00:11:07,010 --> 00:11:11,100
[Ask not until we have won the war.]

157
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:14,600
Everyone!

158
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:18,610
I won't forget any of you after you enter the afterlife!

159
00:11:18,610 --> 00:11:20,950
May you rest in peace!

160
00:11:20,950 --> 00:11:22,640
I'm going to sing a song.

161
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:26,100
"A Thousand Winds"

162
00:11:27,660 --> 00:11:37,620
[A Thousand Winds]
[Performed by Gintoki Sakata]

