00:11:40,550 --> 00:11:47,030
Do not stand at my grave

164
00:11:40,850 --> 00:11:47,140
[Do not stand at my grave]

165
00:11:47,620 --> 00:11:53,910
and weep,

166
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:53,180
[and weep,]

167
00:11:53,910 --> 00:11:59,720
I am not

168
00:11:53,970 --> 00:11:59,510
[I am not there,]

169
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:04,350
not sleep

170
00:11:59,970 --> 00:12:04,140
[I do not sleep.]

171
00:12:04,850 --> 00:12:10,510
[I am a thousand winds]

172
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:17,470
I am a thousand winds

173
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:08,720
Ahh! My guests are going to heaven!

174
00:12:08,870 --> 00:12:11,770
Stop them! Somebody! Stop them!

175
00:12:11,060 --> 00:12:17,140
[I am a thousand winds that blow.]

176
00:12:13,390 --> 00:12:17,470
Brief Trio, go stop them! Or else all of our guests will disappear!

177
00:12:17,740 --> 00:12:22,050
Please wait! Sir Mitsuhide has already made a stairway to heaven!

178
00:12:17,990 --> 00:12:24,400
that blow,

179
00:12:22,050 --> 00:12:24,400
What the hell are you doing?!

180
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:25,940
Come on, Mitsuhide!

181
00:12:25,940 --> 00:12:28,610
Stop! Stop feeding me those heartwarming words.

182
00:12:28,610 --> 00:12:30,280
Or I'm gonna come... I'm gonna come...

183
00:12:30,280 --> 00:12:32,280
Just go now!

184
00:12:34,100 --> 00:12:41,150
I am a thousand winds

185
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:46,800
Damn it! Where did they go?

186
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:50,200
I hear "A Thousand Winds" from all sides.

187
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:52,110
I don't think I can hold it anymore.

188
00:12:52,110 --> 00:12:55,100
Sir Mitsuhide, think of when I killed you!

189
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:57,180
You hate me don't you? You hate me!

190
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:04,560
Sorry, but I have something to tell you before I go.

191
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:06,540
Will you listen to me?

192
00:13:10,770 --> 00:13:14,890
My lord, I'm sorry about Hononji Temple.

193
00:13:17,010 --> 00:13:18,780
Stop! Shoot!

194
00:13:18,780 --> 00:13:20,600
Stop saying, "I have something to say before I go!"

195
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:24,980
Oh shit, oh shit! I'm close to tears. You're doing this on purpose, aren't you?!

196
00:13:24,980 --> 00:13:26,770
My lord! Hold on!

197
00:13:29,050 --> 00:13:30,010
Hideyoshi!

198
00:13:31,940 --> 00:13:35,400
I have one thing to say before I go.

199
00:13:36,010 --> 00:13:39,770
Stop! Stop! I don't want to hear it! I don't!

200
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:44,000
Please return "Armageddon" to the Tsutaya video rental store for me.

201
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,760
Apologize! Say you're sorry for calling me a monkey!

202
00:13:47,680 --> 00:13:49,840
Sir Mitsuhide!

203
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:53,210
Sir Mitsuhide went to heaven from hearing "Armageddon"! What's going on?!

204
00:13:53,210 --> 00:13:53,920
Hey!

205
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:58,390
Oh, I'm sorry. I've confused you with Jean-Claude Van Damme.

206
00:13:58,390 --> 00:14:00,390
Ahh!

207
00:14:00,390 --> 00:14:03,320
Jean-Claude Van Damme! He's so cool!

208
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:06,270
Calm down, monkey! You don't look like him at all!

209
00:14:06,270 --> 00:14:07,530
You're completely Asian!

210
00:14:07,530 --> 00:14:10,170
No, not you. I was referring to you, Mr. Nobunaga.

211
00:14:10,170 --> 00:14:13,360
Ahh! He's awesome! Jean-Claude!

212
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:16,860
My lord! Please calm down. I'm Jean-Claude!

213
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:20,250
Kagura, that's enough. Let's go.

214
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:22,260
Should I finish it?

215
00:14:22,260 --> 00:14:23,390
Oh?

216
00:14:23,390 --> 00:14:24,920
You looked like a really simple guy at first glance,

217
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:26,890
but you're much better looking without glasses.

218
00:14:26,890 --> 00:14:28,760
Arghhh!

219
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:29,710
Shin!

220
00:14:29,710 --> 00:14:32,690
They got me! They got me, but I feel kinda happy!

221
00:14:32,690 --> 00:14:33,680
I did it!

222
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:35,640
Good job, my lord!

223
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:39,100
Ahhh! Don't say good job!

224
00:14:39,430 --> 00:14:41,470
M-M-My lord!

225
00:14:43,490 --> 00:14:47,310
No! Hold on! That's enough! It's over! Hey!

226
00:14:47,790 --> 00:14:48,920
Let's go.

227
00:14:53,180 --> 00:14:56,050
Oh? Did anyone ever tell you that you looked like a celebrity?

228
00:14:56,050 --> 00:14:58,940
Um, who was it? Mi Ito...

229
00:15:02,140 --> 00:15:06,140
Wow, sis, his words didn't move you a bit!

230
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:10,850
Why should they? It's the truth.

231
00:15:20,180 --> 00:15:23,000
I am a thousand...

232
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:24,110
It's useless.

233
00:15:24,630 --> 00:15:27,180
It won't work on my husband.

234
00:15:27,180 --> 00:15:28,440
Is that so?

235
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:32,390
Actually to tell you the truth, except for the main bars, I only vaguely know this song.

236
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:34,750
You sure have done it.

237
00:15:34,750 --> 00:15:37,930
Just what I'd expect from the man I've set my sight on.

238
00:15:38,660 --> 00:15:41,140
But you did a bit too much.

239
00:15:41,560 --> 00:15:45,280
Heh. What's wrong with sending dead people to heaven?

240
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:49,140
Dead people go to the afterlife. It's their natural providence.

241
00:15:49,850 --> 00:15:53,770
Yet you keep them here for no reason.

242
00:15:54,280 --> 00:15:56,890
What do you want to do with them, anyway, old hag?

243
00:16:00,580 --> 00:16:07,570
I don't know what the deal is here, but let's stop licking on each other's wounds.

244
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:12,950
I'll send all of you to the afterlife.

245
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:17,450
Let's just see who will be sent to the afterlife.

246
00:16:30,510 --> 00:16:34,720
Gin, I'll show you what a real Stand user is...

247
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:37,800
...in the worst way possible!

248
00:16:40,060 --> 00:16:43,680
The most powerful Stand, Tagosaku, has finally shown up!

249
00:16:44,170 --> 00:16:48,340
I can feel it even before the battle! This evil aura I feel...

250
00:16:48,340 --> 00:16:52,330
He's totally different from the other Stands!

251
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:56,460
I mean, I see something like "Gogogogo"!

252
00:16:56,460 --> 00:16:59,890
That's the same "Gogogogo" I see in that manga, right?

253
00:16:59,890 --> 00:17:01,070
Yes...

254
00:17:01,490 --> 00:17:04,890
My husband is not just any Stand.

255
00:17:05,440 --> 00:17:09,520
You can't just sing and send him to heaven like everyone else.

256
00:17:09,520 --> 00:17:13,390
He's completely different from other Stands.

257
00:17:13,390 --> 00:17:16,660
Because he has an obsession with this world? Or a grudge?

258
00:17:17,490 --> 00:17:20,760
No, it's because of the bond between two people.

259
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:26,120
For example, a lawyer and defendant, a coach and player,

260
00:17:26,120 --> 00:17:30,490
or Guncannon and Gundam, or Tonkatsu and cabbage, or Mana and Kana!

261
00:17:30,490 --> 00:17:33,640
Hey! The last couple of examples fall short, don't they?!

262
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:37,550
Humph. It means our bond is something that cannot be severed so easily.

263
00:17:37,550 --> 00:17:42,350
Keep that kind of sappy talk to yourself, you old hag!

264
00:17:42,350 --> 00:17:48,560
What? Don't you have a sweetheart? How pathetic!

265
00:17:48,560 --> 00:17:50,670
Oh, leave me alone, you bitch!

266
00:17:51,260 --> 00:17:52,940
I...

267
00:17:58,840 --> 00:18:00,570
Don't take your time if you don't have any!

268
00:18:00,570 --> 00:18:03,280
Shut up! Don't make me miserable!

269
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:06,050
I tend to drag stuff like this out! It really hurts me, you know!

270
00:18:07,260 --> 00:18:09,930
Anyway, it'll be over soon.

271
00:18:12,260 --> 00:18:17,090
No matter when or what it is, Tagosaku will protect me.

272
00:18:18,860 --> 00:18:20,660
Ever since that time...

273
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:30,580
Yes...

274
00:18:31,510 --> 00:18:33,810
He has always protected me.

275
00:18:48,310 --> 00:18:49,660
Always...

276
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:58,960
Is she taking the Stand into her own body?

277
00:18:59,390 --> 00:19:01,140
You have it all wrong.

278
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:06,110
A Stand user is not just about controlling the Stands as you command.

279
00:19:06,660 --> 00:19:09,470
Being able to take in the Stand within your own body,

280
00:19:09,470 --> 00:19:12,060
yet still retaining your own consciousness,

281
00:19:12,060 --> 00:19:14,270
and controlling that immense power.

282
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:17,930
That's a true Stand user.

283
00:19:17,930 --> 00:19:20,960
Gin, can you possibly do this?

284
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:24,770
The old lady's body is transforming into someone else.

285
00:19:24,770 --> 00:19:27,680
This is...a true Stand user?!

286
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:29,950
But you're just His Excellency!

287
00:19:32,350 --> 00:19:35,730
I'll turn you into a wax dummy, too!

288
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:44,060
D-Don't underestimate me, you old hag!

289
00:20:34,760 --> 00:20:39,390
Is that it? We're just getting started here.

290
00:20:39,390 --> 00:20:42,850
Don't tell me you're down already.

291
00:20:48,620 --> 00:20:51,850
Just as I thought, you still have the energy left to move around.

292
00:20:52,810 --> 00:20:53,980
So,

293
00:20:53,980 --> 00:20:55,970
this will be the final blow!

294
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:09,220
Even this isn't enough to atone your sins for wrecking my inn!

295
00:21:09,710 --> 00:21:13,390
An ignorant brat like you talking like you know it all!

296
00:21:13,390 --> 00:21:18,760
It's providence that a dead person goes to the next world. Yes, that's right!

297
00:21:18,760 --> 00:21:22,790
But not everyone can go to heaven.

298
00:21:22,790 --> 00:21:25,720
Some people can't go there!

299
00:21:26,290 --> 00:21:29,380
There're people who can't stop thinking about this world.

300
00:21:29,380 --> 00:21:32,220
Or there're people who have deep scars that have yet to heal.

301
00:21:32,430 --> 00:21:36,430
This is the only place for people like them!

302
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:38,220
You...

303
00:21:38,220 --> 00:21:41,510
You have no right to take it from them!

304
00:21:59,180 --> 00:22:00,680
If that's true,

305
00:22:01,730 --> 00:22:06,590
you don't have the right to keep them here, either, do you?

306
00:22:07,240 --> 00:22:10,750
What keeps them here is not their failure to go to heaven.

307
00:22:10,750 --> 00:22:12,590
Okami, it's because of you!

308
00:22:15,520 --> 00:22:17,220
N-No way.

309
00:22:18,010 --> 00:22:19,570
It can't be!

310
00:22:19,570 --> 00:22:20,560
This is...

311
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:21,940
This is...

312
00:22:25,980 --> 00:22:28,980
You old, dirty hag!

313
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:34,010
[Tou (Sugar)]

314
00:22:28,980 --> 00:22:32,540
I'll make sugar candy out of you!

